Who's News:
   Traub Resigns Post
   At Federated Stores,
   To Form Own Firm
Mr. Traub retired as chairman of Bloomingdale's in
November 1991 but was expected to serve as a vice chairman of
Federated until June 1993. Mr. Traub is launching his new
business in conjunction with former Bloomingdale's vice
chairman Lester Gribetz, who resigned last month.
   Mr. Traub said he has already signed several clients,
include Federated, American Express Co. and Jones New York, a
unit of Jones Apparel Group Inc.
   Mr. Traub, who is finishing an autobiography to be
published in late 1993 by Random House, has taken office
space in Manhattan.